Dear 4:2:2 profile conformance bitstream exchange AHG members,

This is the short version of 4:2:2 profile test bitstream ID 11.  This sequence
contains a flat (uniform) distribution of run/level VLC codes for non-intra
macroblocks.  There are no escape sequences used in the coding of these
macroblocks.  The purpose of this test is to verify that the decoder-under-test
does not rely on the statistically low liklihood of the longer VLCs in the
design of the VLD and rate buffer read bandwidth.

The parameters for the sequence are as follows:

Sequence:	29.97Hz, "Mobile & Calendar", 4 frames, IBBP
Bitrate: 	50 Mbits/sec
Picture size:	720 x 512
VBV size:	9437184 bits
Quant. scale:	Non-uniform (q_scale_type 1)
Picture struct:	Frame
Extras:		Sequence display extension,
		Quantizer Matrix extension with 3 matrices
		Lausanne slice extra information byte,
		Intra DC precision of 11 bits.

The format of the picture data is:

	4:2:2 frame ("display" order) 8 bit samples per compenent.

	width  = 720
	height = 512


                   <--------width--------->
                  +------------------------+
                  |                        |      ^
                  |                        |      |
                  |                        |      |
                  |                        |      |
                  |     Luminance Pels     |    height
                  |                        |      |
                  |                        |      |
                  |                        |      V
                  +-----------+------------+
                  |           |      ^
                  |           |      |
                  |           |      |
                  |  Cb pels  |    height
                  |           |      |
                  |           |      |
                  |           |      V
                  +-----------+      -
                  |           |      ^
                  |           |      |
                  |           |      |
                  |  Cr pels  |    height
                  |           |      |
                  |           |      |
                  |           |      V
                  +-----------+      -
                   <-width/2->

Please email me with the results of your decoding -- also let me know if you
find any errors in this bitstream.

